The paper discusses machine learning techniques for extracting opinion-holder-target structures from text, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural approaches and multi-task learning also suggests a focus on deep learning and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of feature-based models and benchmark datasets also suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and data mining, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
